    • fillWithSnake

      public boolean fillWithSnake(int snakeID, int moveNum, int coorX, int coorY)
      Parameters:
      snakeID - the snake ID holds current snake number to differentiate snakes (1,2,3,...)
      moveNum - the move number is used for counting moves of snakes.
      coorX - the x coordinate of snake - default value is 0
      coorY - the y coordinate of snake - default value is 0
      Returns:
      true if array is filled by snakes otherwise return false

    • moveCheck

      public boolean moveCheck(int x, int y)
      Check validity of next move. Coordinate numbers must not exceed the size of the matrix
      Parameters:
      x - the x coordinate of snake
      y - the y coordinate of snake
      Returns:
      true if next move is valid.
